1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,120
 Can we thank Carla for just being amazing as always?

2
00:00:03,120 --> 00:00:04,160
 So good.

3
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:07,160
 Well, welcome to The Vine.

4
00:00:07,160 --> 00:00:08,760
 My name's Andrew, one of the pastors here.

5
00:00:08,760 --> 00:00:10,400
 And there's probably a lot of you

6
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,040
 that are visiting with us this weekend.

7
00:00:12,040 --> 00:00:14,960
 And we are so, so glad that you are with us and amongst us.

8
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:15,920
 And I know there's loads of people

9
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:16,960
 in the overflow right now.

10
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:19,360
 So I wanted to say hi to everybody in the overflow.

11
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:22,200
 Thank you guys for being willing to sit in the overflow.

12
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,760
 And then everybody that's sitting on the floor

13
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:24,600
 and everything crazy.

14
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:26,840
 Anyway, we're so glad you guys are here.

15
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:28,000
 A number of years ago,

16
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,480
 I was invited to speak at a church overseas.

17
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:34,400
 And this happens a number of times for me.

18
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:37,760
 And it's always a great privilege to travel overseas,

19
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:40,600
 to speak in other churches and other contexts.

20
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:42,920
 But every time I get invited to speak overseas,

21
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:45,280
 I know that I, as well as being excited,

22
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:47,640
 I know that I'm also gonna be exhausted

23
00:00:47,640 --> 00:00:50,360
 because these trips are like full on.

24
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:53,360
 From the moment that the pastor from that church

25
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:54,800
 picks you up at the airport

26
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:56,880
 to the moment that they drop you back at the airport,

27
00:00:56,880 --> 00:01:00,920
 like three days later, you are on 24/7.

28
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:02,560
 It is crazy.

29
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:05,840
 They expect you not just to speak in their church,

30
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:08,480
 but they expect you to sort of pastor all their people,

31
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:10,920
 pray for everybody, solve all the problems of the church,

32
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,760
 work out why their finances are not right,

33
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:15,200
 visit with their eldership and solve all the problems there

34
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,840
 and strategically believe for everything.

35
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:18,120
 You're supposed to have a prophetic word

36
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:19,720
 for every single person in the church.

37
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:21,680
 The whole thing is crazy.

38
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:23,040
 And it is a great privilege.

39
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:25,640
 Honestly, one of the great privileges to go there.

40
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:26,880
 I love what I do.

41
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:28,920
 And when I'm getting invited to go do that,

42
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:30,400
 I'm very excited about it.

43
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:34,440
 But I recognize that I have to manage my energy.

44
00:01:34,440 --> 00:01:38,080
 If I don't manage my energy,

45
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:41,040
 I know that about a day and a half into the trip,

46
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:43,880
 I will hate everybody in that church.

47
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:45,680
 I will be exhausted.

48
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:48,280
 Anyone here not like people when you're tired?

49
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,360
 You know, when you get tired, right?

50
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:51,760
 You get a little prickly with people.

51
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:54,520
 And I realized that I'm going overseas to this church.

52
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:56,120
 I'm representing the vine, right?

53
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:58,880
 I don't wanna be that guy like two days in

54
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:00,920
 who really doesn't like the people around them

55
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,320
 and is getting a little prickly with people.

56
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:05,160
 So I have to like make sure that my energy

57
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,920
 is well managed on these trips.

58
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:09,280
 Well, on this particular trip I went to,

59
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:11,000
 the church was larger than the vine.

60
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,840
 They had five services on a Sunday.

61
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:14,720
 I was speaking at all five services,

62
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:16,520
 pretty much back to back.

63
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:19,520
 After the third service, I was tired.

64
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:22,480
 After the fourth service, I was a little bit wobbly.

65
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:25,920
 After the fifth service, I couldn't even remember my name.

66
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:28,840
 Okay, I was really exhausted.

67
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:31,240
 And of course it was after every service,

68
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,800
 they expected me to be on the prayer line.

69
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,640
 So I'd go down the front, I'd be on the prayer line.

70
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:37,440
 And it was after the fifth service,

71
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:40,040
 I'm on the prayer line after I've just preached.

72
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,120
 There's a crowd of people

73
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:43,440
 that are waiting to get prayed for me

74
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:45,960
 that the most awkward thing

75
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:49,760
 that perhaps has ever happened to me happens.

76
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:53,120
 There was this guy on the prayer line

77
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:55,080
 waiting for me to pray with him.

78
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:58,520
 He comes forward and as usual with these sort of things,

79
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,200
 we introduce ourselves and stuff.

80
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,760
 And I say to him, the thing that I say to pretty much

81
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:04,760
 everybody when I'm ever on a prayer line,

82
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:07,000
 I say to him, what is it that you would like me

83
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,360
 to pray for you for today?

84
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:11,640
 What is it that I can pray for you about?

85
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:15,200
 This was his response.

86
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:19,120
 He said this, "You're a man of God.

87
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:21,720
 "I don't need to tell you what my needs are.

88
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:22,920
 "God knows.

89
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:25,160
 "Just ask God and he will tell you.

90
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:27,240
 "I wanna see what you will say."

91
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:31,240
 (congregation laughing)

92
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:33,120
 Five services, okay?

93
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:36,240
 I'm exhausted and I don't like people at this point.

94
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,440
 All right?

95
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:40,000
 And here's this guy and I tell you what,

96
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,480
 this happens more than you might think,

97
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:43,760
 more than you expect.

98
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:45,480
 This guy comes up to me, he's basically like,

99
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:47,280
 I wanna see whether you're really a pastor.

100
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:49,960
 I wanna see if you really hear from God, okay?

101
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:52,760
 I know what my needs are, God knows, but do you know?

102
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:54,040
 (laughing)

103
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:55,600
 You're gonna have to pray about it

104
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,760
 and when you pray about it,

105
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:59,120
 we'll find out if you hear from the Spirit of God.

106
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:02,440
 (congregation laughing)

107
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:07,320
 By the way, if you're taking notes, write this down.

108
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:11,120
 Us pastors do not like people like this, okay?

109
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,080
 (congregation laughing)

110
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:15,920
 This feels like you're put under a spiritual test.

111
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,840
 It feels like they're testing you

112
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:21,160
 to see whether you're truly a person of the Spirit.

113
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,000
 And so this guy is speaking like this,

114
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,840
 by the way, this is on the same part

115
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:28,560
 as the other pet peeve that us pastors have

116
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:32,440
 and that's this, pastor, you prayed for me seven years ago

117
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:34,120
 and I've never seen you ever since.

118
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,880
 Do you remember what you prayed for?

119
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:38,880
 (congregation laughing)

120
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:43,600
 Here's the answer, no, we don't remember.

121
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,520
 We're like vessels, the Spirit comes in

122
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:48,280
 and out of us, we are not spiritual data cards

123
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:51,760
 that are storing everybody's spiritual issues for decades.

124
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:54,120
 That doesn't happen, okay, anyway.

125
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:57,040
 So this guy is like testing me.

126
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:01,400
 I'm, my attitude, like I am using all the remaining reserves

127
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:04,400
 of energy that I have to try to be calm

128
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:07,800
 and nice and polite to this guy.

129
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,640
 So I said, okay, yeah, sure, let's pray.

130
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:14,120
 So I put my hand on his shoulder, we start to pray

131
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:16,800
 and I say to God, God, you know I'm tired

132
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:21,200
 and you know my attitude really is not good right now.

133
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,840
 But I come to you and if you have something

134
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:25,840
 you wanna say to this guy, speak to me

135
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,360
 and I'll pray over him.

136
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:30,080
 Well, as God often does with me,

137
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:32,320
 he gave me a visual, a visual something.

138
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:34,440
 I often see things when I'm praying for people

139
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:38,040
 and I saw something and I begin to pray this over this guy.

140
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,360
 About a minute into praying it,

141
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:43,640
 I realized that what I'm praying is not very positive.

142
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:47,560
 It's not very sort of happy.

143
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,120
 It's actually kind of a hard thing

144
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,080
 that I was praying for him about.

145
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:53,400
 And I kept praying and I kind of lent into

146
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:56,320
 what I sensed God was saying and as I prayed on,

147
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:59,000
 I could tell that the prayer was just a little bit heavy,

148
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,760
 it was a little bit, it wasn't mean,

149
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:02,880
 but it was just like the things that I felt

150
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:03,720
 like God was saying to him

151
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:06,440
 were not necessarily easy things to hear.

152
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:08,760
 And at the end of the prayer, I said amen

153
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:11,720
 and I opened my eyes and I was met with this face.

154
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:15,200
 (congregation laughing)

155
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,200
 And the guy says these words to me, he goes,

156
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:21,040
 "Uh, okay, thank you."

157
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,960
 And then he just walks off.

158
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:23,800
 And I'm left there like,

159
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:27,680
 "That is the most awkward experience I have ever had."

160
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:31,400
 Well, six months later, I get an email

161
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:33,400
 and the email is from this guy

162
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:35,760
 and he's managed to track down my email.

163
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:37,880
 And in the opening line of the email,

164
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:39,720
 I wonder if you can imagine what it said, it said this,

165
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,520
 "Pastor, you prayed for me six months ago.

166
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:44,120
 I wonder if you remember what you prayed for me about."

167
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:46,600
 (congregation laughing)

168
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,560
 The irony is in this case,

169
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:51,920
 I did actually remember what I prayed for this guy about

170
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:54,360
 'cause it wasn't very nice, right?

171
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:56,320
 And he starts to tell me in this email, he's like,

172
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:58,640
 "You know, you prayed for me and you said these things.

173
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:01,320
 And I was actually really offended in the moment

174
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:03,040
 and I didn't like what you said.

175
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:05,480
 And I walked away and out of the church that day

176
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,640
 and I was angry.

177
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:07,760
 I was angry at you.

178
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,080
 I was angry at God."

179
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:11,200
 And anyway, he just, this was not a pleasant email

180
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,040
 up to this point, right?

181
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,160
 And I was like, "Okay, great."

182
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:15,360
 And then he said, "But you know, God kept speaking to me

183
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:18,800
 about those words that you said over the coming weeks.

184
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:22,520
 And I kept having to bring myself back to prayer

185
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:23,720
 with those words.

186
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:27,080
 And I realized that those words that God was saying to me

187
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:30,800
 on that day were designed to uproot

188
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:33,520
 some of the deepest stuff that was in my life."

189
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:36,200
 And he went on to tell me some of the deep sins

190
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:38,760
 and the brokenness, addictions,

191
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:41,240
 and some things that he had in his life.

192
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:43,360
 And as the email went on, he said,

193
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:46,840
 "You know, I was able, it took me about six months,

194
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:49,280
 but I've been able to reach out to my wife."

195
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:50,400
 It turned out that him and his wife

196
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,320
 had been separated for some time.

197
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:54,880
 And he reached out to his wife and he repented with her

198
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:56,720
 and apologized for some things.

199
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:58,320
 And he said, "We've gotten back together

200
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:00,200
 and we're trying to make marriage work again.

201
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,040
 And I just wanted to let you know

202
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:04,320
 that although I treated you rudely in the moment,

203
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:07,280
 that those things that you said disrupted stuff."

204
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,480
 He goes, he actually said this.

205
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:11,720
 He said, "I didn't wanna hear what you said,

206
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:14,520
 but it disrupted some things in me

207
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:16,480
 that needed to get disrupted."

208
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,560
 And he said, "I just want you to know

209
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,200
 that I'm in a better place now."

210
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:24,200
 I wonder if you've ever experienced God

211
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:27,960
 saying something to you that is not easy for you to hear,

212
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:32,560
 that is not comfortable to hear.

213
00:08:32,560 --> 00:08:34,360
 I wonder if any of us have ever experienced

214
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:37,440
 when God speaks to us in a way that

215
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:42,440
 kinda just comes in and disrupts some things in us.

216
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:44,320
 It's not easy, is it?

217
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,560
 I think as Christians, we often think that

218
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,120
 when God speaks to his people,

219
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:50,920
 he's always gonna speak super positive things.

220
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:52,320
 That when God speaks to his people,

221
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,800
 it's always gonna be kind of a feel good thing.

222
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,200
 It's always gonna make me feel good.

223
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,160
 It's always gonna be great.

224
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:59,000
 It's always gonna be wonderful.

225
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,040
 And I think us Christians get so conditioned

226
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:04,040
 into thinking that that's always how God speaks,

227
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:06,640
 that when God shows up and says something

228
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:08,760
 that's slightly different to what we expected

229
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:11,240
 or says something that we weren't quite

230
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:13,720
 kind of wanting to hear or whatever it might be,

231
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:16,080
 we often, as Christians, I think, reject that.

232
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:17,920
 We think, "Oh, that's probably not God.

233
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:18,840
 That can't be God.

234
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,160
 God wouldn't say something like that."

235
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:22,440
 And we kinda push away from it.

236
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:25,240
 And I think we have this problem as Christians sometimes,

237
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:29,000
 'cause we're always expecting God to show up a certain way,

238
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:31,440
 but when he shows up in a different way,

239
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,520
 we really struggle with that.

240
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:35,120
 Am I the only person here who struggles with that?

241
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:39,720
 I am, I guess, the only person here who struggles with that.

242
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:42,800
 I'm assuming that more of you also do.

243
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:45,960
 Here's the reality that I think I've come to learn

244
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:49,280
 about God that I think is actually a very important thing

245
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:52,680
 for us to grasp, and it's this,

246
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:55,280
 that sometimes when God speaks,

247
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:58,600
 the very thing you need to hear the most

248
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:01,920
 is often the very thing you want to hear the least.

249
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:05,560
 Come on, church.

250
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,200
 So often when God speaks to us,

251
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:10,320
 the very thing we need to hear the most

252
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:14,000
 is often the very thing we want to hear the least.

253
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:18,560
 That actually is a really good summary

254
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:21,400
 of the first Christmas that happened some 2,000 years ago.

255
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:26,720
 See, when Matthew and Luke present the birth story of Jesus,

256
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:30,640
 they present it in a raw and very real way.

257
00:10:30,640 --> 00:10:33,040
 And yes, it's a story of incredible moments,

258
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:36,400
 a story of choirs of angels and God's birth,

259
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,920
 the incarnation and the glory and the peace

260
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:40,920
 that is exclaimed during that time.

