00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,480
 you're gonna be like, "Oh my goodness, I can't believe

548
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:35,520
 he just said that."

549
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:39,560
 This is not gonna be an easy future for you, Mary.

550
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:42,400
 And God so loves Mary in this moment.

551
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:46,200
 So, I want you to see this, so loves Mary,

552
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:49,320
 but sees her future and knows it's gonna be hard,

553
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:52,240
 knows that raising the son of God is not gonna be easy.

554
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:54,080
 And so out of his love for her,

555
00:22:54,080 --> 00:22:56,600
 he wants to prepare her and mold her

556
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:59,840
 and shape her into the woman that she needs to become

557
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:02,440
 so that she can be the mother to the son of God.

558
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:06,240
 And so he brings a word that she may not want to have heard,

559
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:09,680
 but she needed to hear in order to become the woman

560
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:10,920
 God wanted her to become.

561
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:16,440
 I mean, Jesus, can you imagine what Jesus is about to do?

562
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:19,960
 He's about to say things like,

563
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:22,560
 "Unless you eat my flesh and drink my blood,

564
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:24,920
 you have no part of my kingdom."

565
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:28,040
 That one got most of his followers to leave him.

566
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:29,800
 He would say to the religious authorities of the day,

567
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:34,320
 "You brood of vipers, you whitewashed tombs."

568
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:36,160
 He would say to his disciples, the followers,

569
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:38,800
 he would say, "Unless you pick up your cross,

570
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:41,640
 unless you die, basically, you can't follow me."

571
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:44,080
 He would actually say to his best friend,

572
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:47,400
 he would call his best friend Satan.

573
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:50,760
 This is not how to win friends and influence people.

574
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:55,600
 And then Simeon says this.

575
00:23:55,600 --> 00:24:00,120
 He says, "A sword will pierce your own soul too."

576
00:24:00,120 --> 00:24:03,600
 He's not speaking, of course, of a literal sword.

577
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,920
 He's not speaking of her death in the future.

578
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:08,880
 He's speaking about her emotions.

579
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:12,160
 He's speaking about how hard it's going to be for her.

580
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:14,680
 And that if she's not prepared for the reality

581
00:24:14,680 --> 00:24:17,680
 of the chance and the choices and the things,

582
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:19,960
 there's one point Jesus is going to,

583
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:22,100
 in front of his mother, say,

584
00:24:22,100 --> 00:24:24,640
 "My mother and father is not biological.

585
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:27,640
 My mother and father is anyone who follows after my father."

586
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:32,120
 Mary is going to have a hard path.

587
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:37,120
 And God doesn't hold back from helping her to see

588
00:24:37,120 --> 00:24:39,960
 that there's some tough times ahead.

589
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:41,440
 There's a sword that's going to feel

590
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:43,320
 like it pierces your soul.

591
00:24:43,320 --> 00:24:44,400
 It's going to be difficult.

592
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,920
 And God is saying this because he's like,

593
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:48,980
 "I love you so much that I'm going to say

594
00:24:48,980 --> 00:24:50,840
 the very things to you that you need to hear,

595
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:53,800
 even as you're holding an eight-day-old child

596
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:56,000
 in your hands, the future ahead for him.

597
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,480
 He is going to be the savior of the world.

598
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:59,760
 He is the light of revelation to Gentiles.

599
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:01,360
 He is the glory to Israel.

600
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:03,640
 You are going to have the joy of holding him,

601
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:05,640
 but you're also going to feel the pain

602
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:07,680
 that no parent wants to feel,

603
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:10,760
 and that is you're going to watch your child die."

604
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:18,360
 And God has so much love for Mary

605
00:25:20,040 --> 00:25:23,460
 that he's willing to speak a hard word.

606
00:25:23,460 --> 00:25:28,480
 God has so much love for you.

607
00:25:28,480 --> 00:25:32,860
 God sees everything that is ahead of you.

608
00:25:32,860 --> 00:25:38,200
 God loves you so much that he's also willing,

609
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:41,240
 at times, to come and speak over you

610
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:45,880
 and to help, perhaps, you to see that there are some things

611
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:48,440
 that might need to change in your life,

612
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:50,720
 or perhaps tell you that there are some things coming up

613
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:53,200
 that you need to get ready for and prepare for,

614
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:55,240
 'cause if you're not, it's going to be overwhelming,

615
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:59,160
 and it will feel like a sword has pierced your soul, too.

616
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:02,320
 I think sometimes, as Christians,

617
00:26:02,320 --> 00:26:04,060
 we think that when we come to Christ Jesus,

618
00:26:04,060 --> 00:26:07,440
 then everything's going to be absolutely perfect.

619
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:11,320
 The Christmas story shows us a different thing.

620
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:14,160
 And of course, Jesus is our life.

621
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:16,200
 And the wonderful thing that we celebrate at Christmastime

622
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:18,480
 is the arrival of our Savior and our Messiah,

623
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:19,880
 that when we're in relationship with him,

624
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:22,440
 our sin is taken care of, forgiven.

625
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:24,920
 We're released and filled with the fullness of God,

626
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:27,320
 that the same spirit that raised Jesus is found in us,

627
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:30,280
 and that we are found into flourishing, fullness of life,

628
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:32,560
 that we can know the fullness of peace, shalom,

629
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:34,320
 and that we'll have eternal life with him.

630
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:37,840
 There is so much good news in the gospel, so much there,

631
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:40,840
 and God so wants all of that for you

632
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:45,720
 that he's sometimes willing to speak something

633
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:48,880
 that is not going to be easy for you to hear

634
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:50,800
 to ensure that you remain on the path

635
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,240
 that he has for you to be on.

636
00:26:52,240 --> 00:26:58,680
 See, Jesus is not afraid to speak a disruptive word

637
00:26:58,680 --> 00:27:01,520
 to your perfect world if your perfect world

638
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:03,720
 is perfectly misaligned to his perfect will.

639
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:07,320
 He's not afraid to do that.

640
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:11,560
 And it seems weird, doesn't it, on Christmas Eve,

641
00:27:11,560 --> 00:27:14,780
 that this would be a part of the Christmas story,

642
00:27:15,620 --> 00:27:17,380
 but I think it's a part of the Christmas story

643
00:27:17,380 --> 00:27:21,060
 because God is revealing his heart to his people.

644
00:27:21,060 --> 00:27:23,820
 I'm so passionately in love with you,

645
00:27:23,820 --> 00:27:26,900
 and I so passionately want the best for you

646
00:27:26,900 --> 00:27:31,260
 that if there is anything in your life that is misaligned,

647
00:27:31,260 --> 00:27:35,900
 I have the grace and the courage

648
00:27:35,900 --> 00:27:37,700
 to lead you on a different path.

649
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:43,660
 I don't know about you, but I've had the disruptive word

650
00:27:43,660 --> 00:27:46,820
 of God into my life many times over my life.

651
00:27:46,820 --> 00:27:50,900
 I remember when I first quit my job, I was in banking here.

652
00:27:50,900 --> 00:27:53,660
 I was one of those kids that was the banker.

653
00:27:53,660 --> 00:27:56,100
 I wasn't a millionaire by 30, but I was a banker.

654
00:27:56,100 --> 00:28:01,580
 And I felt God calling me out of that marketplace world

655
00:28:01,580 --> 00:28:04,900
 into being a pastor, and so I remember quitting my job

656
00:28:04,900 --> 00:28:07,020
 and moving with my family to New Zealand

657
00:28:07,020 --> 00:28:07,900
 to go to Bible school,

658
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:09,580
 and I remember the first month in Bible school,

659
00:28:09,580 --> 00:28:11,700
 I felt so excited.

660
00:28:11,700 --> 00:28:13,700
 I felt so excited about what my future was.

661
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:15,780
 I could not wait to become a pastor,

662
00:28:15,780 --> 00:28:17,580
 could not wait to become a preacher.

663
00:28:17,580 --> 00:28:19,180
 I knew that God had called me to preach,

664
00:28:19,180 --> 00:28:21,300
 and I was really excited to have a life

665
00:28:21,300 --> 00:28:23,660
 where I could communicate God's word to people

666
00:28:23,660 --> 00:28:25,540
 and speak life over people.

667
00:28:25,540 --> 00:28:27,580
 I mean, it was everything I wanted to do.

668
00:28:27,580 --> 00:28:29,580
 And I remember in the first month of Bible school,

669
00:28:29,580 --> 00:28:32,220
 I was setting myself ready for all the studies.

670
00:28:32,220 --> 00:28:34,180
 I wanted to learn Greek, I wanted to learn Hebrew.

671
00:28:34,180 --> 00:28:36,180
 I wanted to understand the Bible as best I could

672
00:28:36,180 --> 00:28:37,620
 'cause I wanted to be the best preacher

673
00:28:37,620 --> 00:28:38,980
 of God's word that I could.

674
00:28:38,980 --> 00:28:41,060
 And in the first month, I said to God,

675
00:28:41,060 --> 00:28:43,140
 I said, "God, would you speak to me a word

676
00:28:43,140 --> 00:28:44,660
 about my preaching gift?"

677
00:28:44,660 --> 00:28:49,540
 And I was expecting that God would say,

678
00:28:49,540 --> 00:28:51,820
 "You're awesome, Andrew.

679
00:28:51,820 --> 00:28:53,420
 You're the best ever.

680
00:28:53,420 --> 00:28:54,340
 You're the best.

681
00:28:54,340 --> 00:28:55,820
 I see your future.

682
00:28:55,820 --> 00:28:56,780
 You're gonna be the state apostle

683
00:28:56,780 --> 00:28:58,060
 for a church called the Violet in Hong Kong,

684
00:28:58,060 --> 00:28:59,020
 and it's gonna be amazing.

685
00:28:59,020 --> 00:29:00,620
 And there's gonna be so many people on Christmas Eve

686
00:29:00,620 --> 00:29:02,140
 that not only are you gonna be able to fit into the building

687
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:03,620
 and it's gonna be great."

688
00:29:03,620 --> 00:29:05,660
 (congregation laughing)

689
00:29:05,660 --> 00:29:10,660
 I was expecting a word along those kinds of lines.

690
00:29:11,660 --> 00:29:13,900
 But God said to me, "You really want me to speak to you

691
00:29:13,900 --> 00:29:15,460
 about your preaching gift?"

692
00:29:15,460 --> 00:29:17,140
 And I was like, "Yeah."

693
00:29:17,140 --> 00:29:20,180
 He's like, "Go to Amos chapter eight."

694
00:29:20,180 --> 00:29:23,460
 So I went to Amos chapter eight, and here's what I read.

695
00:29:23,460 --> 00:29:25,740
 "The days are coming, declares the sovereign Lord,

696
00:29:25,740 --> 00:29:27,860
 when I will send a famine through the land,

697
00:29:27,860 --> 00:29:30,420
 not a famine of food or of thirst for water,

698
00:29:30,420 --> 00:29:33,980
 but a famine of hearing the words of the Lord.

699
00:29:33,980 --> 00:29:35,900
 People will stagger from sea to sea

700
00:29:35,900 --> 00:29:37,420
 and wander from north to east,

701
00:29:37,420 --> 00:29:39,460
 searching for the word of the Lord,

702
00:29:39,460 --> 00:29:41,540
 but they will not find it."

703
00:29:41,540 --> 00:29:45,740
 I had asked God to speak to me about my preaching gift,

704
00:29:45,740 --> 00:29:48,260
 and he brings me to this passage where he's like,

705
00:29:48,260 --> 00:29:51,380
 "Andrew, you need to understand that in your life,

706
00:29:51,380 --> 00:29:56,060
 if you don't make some changes, a famine is coming on you,

707
00:29:56,060 --> 00:29:58,380
 and that famine will be on hearing the word of God.

708
00:29:58,380 --> 00:30:01,100
 And you need to understand that what makes a preacher

709
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:02,940
 is not how they speak the words of God,

710
00:30:02,940 --> 00:30:04,700
 but how they hear the words of God.

711
00:30:04,700 --> 00:30:09,100
 I am nothing if I can't hear the words of God.

712
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:11,020
 I am the worst pastor ever.

713
00:30:11,020 --> 00:30:13,540
 I have nothing to say on this stage,

714
00:30:13,540 --> 00:30:17,900
 week in and week out, if I can't hear the words of God.

715
00:30:17,900 --> 00:30:19,740
 If I can't receive and hear something

716
00:30:19,740 --> 00:30:22,100
 and do my best to package it and bring it to you,

717
00:30:22,100 --> 00:30:26,900
 if I can't do that, then this is absolutely useless."

718
00:30:26,900 --> 00:30:29,660
 And I sat there under this idea that God's saying,

719
00:30:29,660 --> 00:30:32,180
 "You really want me to speak about your preaching gift?

720
00:30:32,180 --> 00:30:33,780
 Here's what you need to hear.

721
00:30:33,780 --> 00:30:35,780
 It's not what you want to hear, Andrew,

722
00:30:35,780 --> 00:30:36,900
 but here's what you need to hear.

723
00:30:36,900 --> 00:30:39,220
 A famine is coming on your life

724
00:30:39,220 --> 00:30:41,660
 where you will be completely useless,

725
00:30:41,660 --> 00:30:43,460
 no matter how much Bible knowledge you have,

726
00:30:43,460 --> 00:30:45,220
 no matter how much Greek and Hebrew you might know,

727
00:30:45,220 --> 00:30:47,860
 completely useless unless you change

728
00:30:47,860 --> 00:30:49,100
 some things in your life.

729
00:30:49,100 --> 00:30:51,460
 There's some stuff in your heart, Andrew,

730
00:30:51,460 --> 00:30:53,060
 that you need to deal with.

731
00:30:53,060 --> 00:30:55,220
 And if those things don't get dealt with,

732
00:30:55,220 --> 00:30:58,500
 I will block your ears and you won't hear my word."

733
00:30:58,500 --> 00:31:03,380
 And this led me on a difficult six-month journey

734
00:31:04,780 --> 00:31:07,220
 of dealing with some really important things

735
00:31:07,220 --> 00:31:10,180
 in my soul and my heart that needed to be dealt with,

736
00:31:10,180 --> 00:31:11,260
 things like pride,

737
00:31:11,260 --> 00:31:16,180
 things like arrogance in my cool in life,

738
00:31:16,180 --> 00:31:17,220
 things like thinking I'm better

739
00:31:17,220 --> 00:31:20,020
 because I'm in Bible school than in the marketplace,

740
00:31:20,020 --> 00:31:22,820
 things that were ugly in me,

741
00:31:22,820 --> 00:31:25,220
 other things that I don't want to tell you about.

742
00:31:25,220 --> 00:31:27,540
 And I went through a six-month journey

743
00:31:27,540 --> 00:31:29,940
 of having to bring those things to the Lord

744
00:31:29,940 --> 00:31:31,780
 and have Him deal with me in

745
00:31:33,020 --> 00:31:35,220
 so that I could even think about being

746
00:31:35,220 --> 00:31:36,620
 in the place that I'm in right now

747
00:31:36,620 --> 00:31:39,860
 and doing what I'm doing with you right now.

748
00:31:39,860 --> 00:31:42,940
 And every single time that I prepare a sermon

749
00:31:42,940 --> 00:31:47,340
 here at the Vine, God breathes over me and says,

750
00:31:47,340 --> 00:31:49,820
 "Don't forget Amos 8."

751
00:31:49,820 --> 00:31:56,260
 This has been a disruptive word for me

752
00:31:56,260 --> 00:32:00,500
 that has messed me up inside for years and years and years.

753
00:32:00,500 --> 00:32:03,860
 And by God's grace has enabled me

754
00:32:03,860 --> 00:32:06,020
 to hopefully stand in front of you

755
00:32:06,020 --> 00:32:09,060
 and say some things at times that are helpful to you.

756
00:32:09,060 --> 00:32:16,340
 Mary, Mary had this future ahead of her that God could see.

757
00:32:16,340 --> 00:32:21,180
 And so he came in the gentleness of this amazing man, Simeon,

758
00:32:21,180 --> 00:32:24,060
 and said some things to her that were not easy to hear,

759
00:32:24,060 --> 00:32:27,220
 some things that messed some things up inside of her.

760
00:32:28,500 --> 00:32:30,540
 God could see what my future was

761
00:32:30,540 --> 00:32:33,780
 as a young 30-year-old wondering what was going on in life.

762
00:32:33,780 --> 00:32:37,100
 He could see what was gonna happen for me.

763
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:39,140
 And he said, "You will be a disaster

764
00:32:39,140 --> 00:32:40,420
 "for those people in Hong Kong

765
00:32:40,420 --> 00:32:43,180
 "unless you first deal with this."

766
00:32:43,180 --> 00:32:48,180
 He so loved me and you that he was willing to disrupt

767
00:32:48,180 --> 00:32:51,660
 and make a mess of some things in my life.

768
00:32:51,660 --> 00:32:52,900
 And what you need to understand

769
00:32:52,900 --> 00:32:55,540
 is that God doesn't just come into mess.

770
00:32:55,540 --> 00:32:57,500
 Sometimes He creates mess.

771
00:32:58,300 --> 00:33:01,340
 And He creates a mess sometimes by bringing a word

772
00:33:01,340 --> 00:33:05,140
 that is designed to disrupt some faulty old ways

773
00:33:05,140 --> 00:33:07,740
 of thinking in you so that you would be brought

774
00:33:07,740 --> 00:33:11,540
 into new and transformative ways of being.

775
00:33:11,540 --> 00:33:15,900
 That's actually the Christmas story,

776
00:33:15,900 --> 00:33:21,500
 that Jesus was willing to disrupt this world,

777
00:33:21,500 --> 00:33:25,780
 willing in the incarnation to come and stir some things up

778
00:33:25,780 --> 00:33:28,420
 so that the world would get a vision of a life

